    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Species of deciduous shrub or small tree native to Japan, North Korea, South Korea, China, Mongolia, and southeast Russia; reaching 10 meters in height and typically an understory plant in shady woodlands. The tree may have multiple trunks joining close to the ground. Many different cultivars of this maple have been developed; even in the wild, seedlings from the same parent display remarkable variation in color and shape of leaves. </Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
        <Note_Contributors>
